      "text": "Now turn to coherent control with quantum feedback. Here our controller possesses a quantum subsystem that can be made to interact with the quantum system to be controlled. This interaction allows the system to exchange quantum information with the controller. The exchange of quantum information is not possible when the controller is classical. In addition, we may be able to apply coherent control as above, applying quantum potentials to the system and the quantum subsystem of the controller together."
